        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 5:16PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 515 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Shawnee, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Junction City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
